{"TopicId":202767,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"\u0026quot;Bending\u0026quot; the Laws of Physics for the most difficult law of physics.","CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T19:28:42Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T19:28:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/jyQwgBAaBag?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can beat the wind using the wind itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022unknown.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002290.00\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/461923895528914955/848280737546240041/unknown.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWonder if we can do the opposite way (going upwind with nothing but windpower)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T19:53:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCan. Doing loops.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T19:55:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223981176\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022202767\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221622316522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can beat the wind using the wind itself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWonder if we can do the opposite way (going upwind with nothing but windpower)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming the \u0022cylindrical Earth\u0022 argument is valid, you can sail two ships against the wind (one of the first things a sailor learns is how to tack).\u00A0 Not sure if the \u0022use the wheels to drive the fan\u0022 method will work, but presumably it is possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spica","CreatedById":65153,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T20:14:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223981176\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022202767\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221622316522\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002298447\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022YNM\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n42 minutes ago, YNM said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWonder if we can do the opposite way (going upwind with nothing but windpower)...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou absolutely can, all you need to do is attach a rotor that\u0027s twisted the other way to the same vehicle.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that case, the rotor will act like a turbine that slows the air in the car-fixed frame, and uses that power to drive the wheels.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-29T20:24:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223981188\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022202767\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221622318147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAssuming the \u0022cylindrical Earth\u0022 argument is valid, you can sail two ships against the wind (one of the first things a sailor learns is how to tack).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah I was wondering because of this. There are sail plans that can go very close to the wind and make good progress.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"FleshJeb","CreatedById":111640,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-05-30T01:56:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou folks know what to do (If I still played KSP, I\u0027d be working on it now):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022202988\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9156446773\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/199347-18x-111x-kerbal-weather-project-kwp-v100/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-06-30T20:01:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExtra explanation up (sorry about the title though) \u003Cspan\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022113\u0022 width=\u0022200\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/yCsgoLc_fzI?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T09:42:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe demo with plank and a \u0022cart\u0022 made of rollers is all you really need to understand. If you understand why the cart can outrace the plank that\u0027s pushing it in that demo, you shouldn\u0027t have any trouble understanding why same works with the wind or any other fluid.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-01T16:42:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRegarding sailing directly up the wind, Kevin Costner settled that 25 years ago.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnrelated, but a few years before Kevin trimaraned, when I was but a wee lad if about 5, I distincrly remember playing with yoyo placed on the floor and tugging the string. Yoyo would catch up with my hand.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}